Inputs\: keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable. Returns\: The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable. Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value. notNull - if some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned. 6795f2bb-7c31-4808-92d1-f79dfa7683f7.1b924f53-9929-40d5-8979-5fd7e119aac5.transition.description=unable to check file modification date. 6795f2bb-7c31-4808-92d1-f79dfa7683f7.28eaa949-f4f1-4959-ae3d-b74165b096f4.description= 
Compares a files last modified date/time to a given threshold.

Input Parameters\:
source - the file to read
Threshold - the threshold to compare the file modified time to.
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The file probably could not be found.
greater than	- The file's modified time is larger than the threshold.
less than		- The file's modified time is smaller than the threshold.
equal to		- The file's modified time is the same as the threshold.

Extra Results\:
date			- The file's modified time.

Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. Checks to see if a path points to a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - the path to check
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The path does not point to a directory.
success			- The operation succeeded.
6795f2bb-7c31-4808-92d1-f79dfa7683f7.b1e40b7b-696a-40f4-8361-afd1e973efed.description= 
Gets a list of files and folders in a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - the directory to check
delimiter - A delimiter to put between files and folders in the directory.
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

returns\:
The children of the path.

Extra Results\:
count - the number of children.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The path probably could not be found, or was a file.
success			- The operation succeeded.

6795f2bb-7c31-4808-92d1-f79dfa7683f7.description=
moves or removes windows log files from a folder.

Inputs\:
alternateStore - Where to put log files. They are deleted if null.
folder - Folder to clean of windows log files.
user - user to authenticate as.
password - password for user.
Old Threshold - Files before this date will be cleaned.

Responses\:
success - operation completed.
failure - something went wrong.
